# Research: LLM Wiki / Company Brain / Agent Memory — GitHub Code Analysis

## Summary

This brief analyzes how 10+ OSS projects implement agent memory / knowledge systems by reading **actual source code** on GitHub. The dominant patterns are: (1) pluggable storage backends with vector+graph hybrid architectures, (2) LLM-driven entity extraction during ingestion, (3) bi-temporal versioning for stale knowledge (Graphiti) or LLM-based ADD/UPDATE/DELETE conflict resolution (Mem0), and (4) multi-tenant isolation via `group_id`/`user_id`/`tenant_id` partition keys. MongoDB is used natively only by **Mem0** (as a first-class vector store with Atlas Vector Search); **Letta** supports MongoDB as external archival memory. No other repo uses MongoDB or a document store as a primary backend — the field is split between graph databases (Neo4j/Kuzu/FalkorDB), vector databases (Qdrant/LanceDB), and file-based markdown (OpenWiki/OKF/Cline).

---

## Per-Repo Findings (from CODE)

### 1. LangChain OpenWiki (`langchain-ai/openwiki`)

**Data Model/Schema:**
- File-based. No database. The core TypeScript types are in `src/agent/types.ts`.
- `UpdateMetadata` interface: `{ updatedAt: string; command: OpenWikiCommand; gitHead?: string; model: string }` — tracks last Git commit SHA for incremental updates.
  - [src/agent/types.ts#L29-34](https://github.com/langchain-ai/openwiki/blob/main/src/agent/types.ts#L29-L34)
- `RunContext`: `{ lastUpdate: UpdateMetadata | null; gitSummary: string }` — ephemeral state per execution.
  - [src/agent/types.ts#L36-39](https://github.com/langchain-ai/openwiki/blob/main/src/agent/types.ts#L36-L39)
- `OpenWikiCommand = "chat" | "init" | "update"` — three operational modes.
  - [src/agent/types.ts#L1](https://github.com/langchain-ai/openwiki/blob/main/src/agent/types.ts#L1)

**Storage Backend:** Files (Markdown) + Git. No vector/graph/doc store. Knowledge is stored as structured Markdown in `openwiki/` directory with cross-references for LLM retrieval. Storage choice: human-readable, diffable, agent-readable without SDK.

**Ingestion Pipeline:** Git-diff driven. Compares current HEAD to `gitHead` in `.last-update.json`, sends relevant code snippets + current wiki state to LLM, LLM generates updated Markdown.

**Retrieval Pipeline:** No programmatic retrieval — relies on LLM agent reading the `openwiki/` markdown files directly. `AGENTS.md`/`CLAUDE.md` gets a reference section pointing agents to the wiki.

**Updates/Stale Knowledge:** Incremental via Git. `gitHead` SHA in metadata tracks last-documented commit. Only changed code since last SHA is re-documented.

**Multi-Tenant:** None — per-repository only. No user/company isolation.

**MongoDB:** No.

---

### 2. Google Open Knowledge Format / OKF (`GoogleCloudPlatform/knowledge-catalog`)

**Data Model/Schema:**
- Spec at `okf/SPEC.md`. Format: directory of Markdown files with YAML frontmatter. No database, no schema registry.
- **Knowledge Bundle** = self-contained hierarchical collection of knowledge documents (the unit of distribution).
  - [okf/SPEC.md#L40-42](https://github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/knowledge-catalog/blob/main/okf/SPEC.md#L40-L42)
- **Concept** = single unit of knowledge = one markdown document. May describe a tangible asset (table, API) or abstract idea (metric, playbook).
  - [okf/SPEC.md#L44-47](https://github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/knowledge-catalog/blob/main/okf/SPEC.md#L44-L47)
- **Concept ID** = file path with `.md` removed (e.g., `tables/users.md` → concept ID `tables/users`).
  - [okf/SPEC.md#L49-51](https://github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/knowledge-catalog/blob/main/okf/SPEC.md#L49-L51)
- **Frontmatter schema** (§4.1):
  - Required: `type` (short string, not centrally registered — producers pick descriptive values, consumers tolerate unknown types)
  - Recommended: `title`, `description`, `resource` (canonical URI), `tags` (list of strings), `timestamp` (ISO 8601)
  - Extensions: producers MAY include any additional keys; consumers SHOULD preserve unknown keys
  - [okf/SPEC.md#L104-134](https://github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/knowledge-catalog/blob/main/okf/SPEC.md#L104-L134)
- **Reserved filenames**: `index.md` (directory listing for progressive disclosure), `log.md` (update history).
  - [okf/SPEC.md#L82-89](https://github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/knowledge-catalog/blob/main/okf/SPEC.md#L82-L89)
- **Body**: standard markdown. Conventional headings: `# Schema`, `# Examples`, `# Citations`.
  - [okf/SPEC.md#L151-157](https://github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/knowledge-catalog/blob/main/okf/SPEC.md#L151-L157)
- **Links** = standard markdown links between concepts (expresses relationships beyond parent/child hierarchy).
  - [okf/SPEC.md#L53](https://github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/knowledge-catalog/blob/main/okf/SPEC.md#L53)

**Storage Backend:** Files only. Markdown + YAML frontmatter. Distributable as git repo (recommended — provides history, attribution, diffs), tarball, or subdirectory. Storage choice: "If you can `cat` a file, you can read OKF; if you can `git clone` a repo, you can ship it." Explicitly a non-goal: "Prescribing storage, serving, or query infrastructure."
  - [okf/SPEC.md#L12-14](https://github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/knowledge-catalog/blob/main/okf/SPEC.md#L12-L14)
  - [okf/SPEC.md#L33-34](https://github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/knowledge-catalog/blob/main/okf/SPEC.md#L33-L34)

**Ingestion Pipeline:** N/A — OKF is a format spec, not a pipeline. Authored by people or generated by agents.

**Retrieval Pipeline:** N/A — format only. Consumption agents traverse directory structure, read frontmatter for routing/filtering, follow markdown links.

**Updates/Stale Knowledge:** `timestamp` field in frontmatter (ISO 8601 last-modified). `log.md` for chronological update history. Git provides versioning/diffs.

**Multi-Tenant:** Bundle-level isolation — each Knowledge Bundle is self-contained and distributable independently.

**MongoDB:** No.

---

### 3. Mem0 (`mem0ai/mem0`)

**Data Model/Schema:**
- `MemoryItem` (Pydantic BaseModel) in `mem0/configs/base.py`:
  - `id: str`, `memory: str` (extracted fact), `hash: Optional[str]` (MD5 dedup), `metadata: Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` (user_id, agent_id, app_id, run_id, category), `score: Optional[float]`, `created_at: Optional[str]`, `updated_at: Optional[str]`
  - [mem0/configs/base.py#L17-26](https://github.com/mem0ai/mem0/blob/main/mem0/configs/base.py#L17-L26)
- `MemoryConfig` (Pydantic): `vector_store`, `llm`, `embedder`, `history_db_path` (SQLite at `~/.mem0/history.db`), `reranker: Optional[RerankerConfig]`, `version: str = "v1.1"`, `custom_instructions`
  - [mem0/configs/base.py#L29-57](https://github.com/mem0ai/mem0/blob/main/mem0/configs/base.py#L29-L57)

**Storage Backend:** Pluggable provider pattern:
- **Vector stores**: Qdrant (primary), ChromaDB, Pinecone, Weaviate, Milvus, Redis, Valkey, PGVector, **MongoDB** (Atlas Vector Search)
- **Relational/metadata**: SQLite (default local), PostgreSQL
- **Graph**: Neo4j, Amazon Neptune, Memgraph (optional, restructured in recent versions)
- Storage choice rationale: modular — each DB has its own implementation file in `mem0/vector_stores/`

**Ingestion Pipeline:** Three-stage:
1. **Extraction**: LLM (GPT-4o default) processes conversation to extract discrete facts. Single-pass ADD-only in v1.1+.
2. **Consolidation**: System determines if facts contradict/update/supplement existing memories (A.U.D.N. cycle via `DEFAULT_UPDATE_MEMORY_PROMPT` in `mem0/configs/prompts.py`).
3. **Embedding**: OpenAI `text-embedding-3-small` default (1536 dims), pluggable via `EmbedderConfig`.

**Retrieval Pipeline:** Multi-signal hybrid search:
- Vector similarity (cosine) via configured vector store
- Exact keyword matching (BM25 / Atlas Search text index)
- Entity linking for multi-hop boost
- Optional reranker (`RerankerConfig`)
  - [mem0/configs/base.py#L48-51](https://github.com/mem0ai/mem0/blob/main/mem0/configs/base.py#L48-L51)

**Updates/Stale Knowledge/Conflict Resolution:**
- LLM-driven A.U.D.N. cycle: ADD (new fact), UPDATE (enriches old), DELETE (contradicts old), NOOP (redundant)
- MD5 hash dedup before LLM step (saves cost) — `hash` field on MemoryItem
- "Latest truth wins" — most recent user input is canonical when contradiction detected
- `created_at`/`updated_at` timestamps for temporal reasoning
- No bi-temporal model — old memories are overwritten/deleted, not versioned

**Multi-Tenant:** Via metadata scoping: `user_id`, `agent_id`, `app_id`, `run_id` in metadata dict. Data is logically isolated by these IDs — personalized memory per user or shared across agent fleet.

**MongoDB Usage (CONFIRMED IN CODE):**
- `mem0/vector_stores/mongodb.py` — first-class `MongoDB(VectorStoreBase)` implementation
- Uses `pymongo` + Atlas Vector Search (`SearchIndexModel` with `type="vectorSearch"`, `similarity="cosine"`)
- Also creates Atlas Search text index for keyword search (fields: `payload.data`, `payload.text_lemmatized`)
- Document schema: `{"_id": id, "embedding": vector, "payload": payload}` — unifies document + vector in single collection
  - [mem0/vector_stores/mongodb.py#L1-16](https://github.com/mem0ai/mem0/blob/main/mem0/vector_stores/mongodb.py#L1-L16)
  - [mem0/vector_stores/mongodb.py#L38-44](https://github.com/mem0ai/mem0/blob/main/mem0/vector_stores/mongodb.py#L38-L44)
  - [mem0/vector_stores/mongodb.py#L81-110](https://github.com/mem0ai/mem0/blob/main/mem0/vector_stores/mongodb.py#L81-L110)
  - [mem0/vector_stores/mongodb.py#L141-148](https://github.com/mem0ai/mem0/blob/main/mem0/vector_stores/mongodb.py#L141-L148) (insert: document = {"_id", "embedding", "payload"})

---

### 4. Letta / MemGPT (`letta-ai/letta`)

**Data Model/Schema:**
- **Memory Block** = primary abstraction (always visible to agent in context window):
  - `label: str` (unique ID, e.g., "human", "persona"), `description: str` (instructions for agent), `value: str` (actual content), `limit: int` (character limit), `metadata: dict` (e.g., `chars_current` for budgeting)
- Memory blocks compiled into XML-like format and prepended to system prompt (non-retrieval based)
- **Context Repositories (MemFS)**: memory stored in git-backed directory (`~/.letta/agents/<id>/memory/`), each block projected as Markdown file — enables version control, audit trails, human editing that syncs back

**Storage Backend:**
- **Internal state** (agent metadata, message history, tool definitions): PostgreSQL or SQLite (Prisma ORM)
- **External archival memory**: pluggable — MongoDB Atlas, PgVector, ChromaDB, etc. (agent queries via tool calls = "Agentic RAG")
- Storage choice: in-context blocks = "RAM", archival = "hard drive" — LLM swaps context in/out

**Ingestion Pipeline:** Agent self-edits memory blocks via tool calls (`core_memory_append`, `core_memory_replace`, `core_memory_remove`). No automated extraction pipeline — the agent decides what to remember.

**Retrieval Pipeline:**
- Core memory: always in context (no retrieval needed)
- Archival memory: agent uses `archival_memory_search` tool (vector search via configured backend)
- "Agentic RAG" — agent decides when/what to retrieve, not pre-fetched by developer

**Updates/Stale Knowledge:** Agent self-manages via tool calls. Git-backed MemFS provides version history. No automatic conflict resolution — agent is responsible for updating its own blocks.

**Multi-Tenant:** Per-agent isolation (each agent has own ID, own memory blocks, own archival store). No explicit company/tenant partitioning at the storage level.

**MongoDB:** Supported as external archival memory provider (tool-based, not internal state). Not used for core memory blocks.

---

### 5. Graphiti / Zep (`getzep/graphiti`)

**Data Model/Schema:**
- `graphiti_core/nodes.py` — Pydantic models:
  - **`Node` (ABC)**: `uuid: str`, `name: str`, `group_id: str` (partition key), `labels: list[str]`, `created_at: datetime`
    - [graphiti_core/nodes.py#L53-59](https://github.com/getzep/graphiti/blob/main/graphiti_core/nodes.py#L53-L59)
  - **`EpisodeType` (Enum)**: `message`, `json`, `text`, `fact_triple`
    - [graphiti_core/nodes.py#L39-52](https://github.com/getzep/graphiti/blob/main/graphiti_core/nodes.py#L39-L52)
  - **`EpisodicNode(Node)`**: `source: EpisodeType`, `source_description: str`, `content: str` (raw episode data), `valid_at: datetime` (when original document was created), `entity_edges: list[str]`, `episode_metadata: dict[str, Any] | None`
    - [graphiti_core/nodes.py#L321-331](https://github.com/getzep/graphiti/blob/main/graphiti_core/nodes.py#L321-L331)
  - **`EntityNode(Node)`**: `name_embedding: list[float] | None`, `summary: str` (regional summary of surrounding edges), `attributes: dict[str, Any]`
    - [graphiti_core/nodes.py#L251-256](https://github.com/getzep/graphiti/blob/main/graphiti_core/nodes.py#L251-L256)
- `graphiti_core/edges.py` — Pydantic models:
  - **`Edge` (ABC)**: `uuid: str`, `group_id: str`, `source_node_uuid: str`, `target_node_uuid: str`, `created_at: datetime`
    - [graphiti_core/edges.py#L42-46](https://github.com/getzep/graphiti/blob/main/graphiti_core/edges.py#L42-L46)
  - **`EntityEdge(Edge)`**: `name: str` (relation name), `fact: str` (fact representing edge + connected nodes), `fact_embedding: list[float] | None`, `episodes: list[str]`, **`expired_at: datetime | None`** (system invalidation), **`valid_at: datetime | None`** (fact became true), **`invalid_at: datetime | None`** (fact stopped being true), `reference_time: datetime | None`, `attributes: dict[str, Any]`
    - [graphiti_core/edges.py#L257-276](https://github.com/getzep/graphiti/blob/main/graphiti_core/edges.py#L257-L276)

**Storage Backend:** Graph database only. Supports: **Neo4j**, **Kuzu**, **FalkorDB**, **Amazon Neptune**. No vector store — embeddings stored as node/edge properties within graph (`name_embedding`, `fact_embedding`). Storage choice: temporal knowledge graph requires relationship traversal + bi-temporal queries that graph DBs excel at.

**Ingestion Pipeline:**
1. Episode ingested (message/json/text/fact_triple)
2. LLM extracts entities and relationships (edges/facts)
3. Entity name embeddings generated via `EmbedderClient`
4. Edge fact embeddings generated
5. Nodes/edges saved to graph DB with provider-specific Cypher queries

**Retrieval Pipeline:**
- Hybrid: vector similarity (fact/name embeddings stored in graph) + graph traversal
- Entity edges retrieved by embedding similarity, then graph traversal for connected context
- Episodic nodes linked to entities via `MENTIONS` edges
- Community nodes for clustered summaries

**Updates/Stale Knowledge/Temporal Versioning (KEY DIFFERENTIATOR):**
- **Bi-temporal model**: 4 timestamps per edge:
  - `valid_at` (real-world: when fact became true)
  - `invalid_at` (real-world: when fact stopped being true)
  - `created_at` (system: when fact was ingested)
  - `expired_at` (system: when system learned fact was superseded)
    - [graphiti_core/edges.py#L265-272](https://github.com/getzep/graphiti/blob/main/graphiti_core/edges.py#L265-L272)
- **Conflict resolution**: Old edge NOT deleted — `expired_at` set to current time. New edge created. Supersession pointer links new→old. Creates versioned chain of facts.
- **Point-in-time queries**: World-state ("what was true on Jan 1?") filters `valid_at <= date AND (invalid_at > date OR null)`. Knowledge-state ("what did system believe?") filters `created_at <= date AND (expired_at > date OR null)`.

**Multi-Tenant:** `group_id` field on every Node and Edge — partition of the graph. All queries filter by `group_id`. `delete_by_group_id` for full tenant deletion.
  - [graphiti_core/nodes.py#L55](https://github.com/getzep/graphiti/blob/main/graphiti_core/nodes.py#L55)
  - [graphiti_core/nodes.py#L139-174](https://github.com/getzep/graphiti/blob/main/graphiti_core/nodes.py#L139-L174)

**MongoDB:** No.

