### 7. Microsoft GraphRAG (`microsoft/graphrag`)

**Data Model/Schema:**
- `python/graphrag/graphrag/model/entity.py` — **`Entity` (dataclass)**:
  - `id: str`, `title: str`, `short_id: str | None`, `type: str | None`, `description: str | None`, `description_embedding: list[float] | None`, `graph_embedding: list[float] | None`, `community_ids: list[str] | None`, `text_unit_ids: list[str] | None`, `document_ids: list[str] | None`, `rank: int | None`, `attributes: dict[str, Any] | None`
  - [entity.py#L8-43](https://github.com/microsoft/graphrag/blob/main/python/graphrag/graphrag/model/entity.py#L8-L43)
- Additional model types (from docs/parquet outputs): **Document** (original input file, contains TextUnits), **TextUnit** (chunk ~300-1200 tokens), **Relationship** (edge: source, target, weight, description), **Community** (hierarchical cluster of entities), **CommunityReport** (LLM-generated summary of community), **Covariate** (optional temporal/claim entities)

**Storage Backend:**
- **Tabular**: Parquet files (entities.parquet, relationships.parquet, text_units.parquet, documents.parquet, communities.parquet, community_reports.parquet, covariates.parquet) — output of indexing pipeline
- **Vector**: LanceDB (embedded, `.lance` files) — for entity_description, text_unit_text, community_full_content embeddings
- **Graph**: outputs as Parquet (not a live graph DB) — graph structure is materialized during indexing, queried via search engines
- Storage choice: Parquet for portability + LanceDB for local vector search. No server-side database required.

**Ingestion Pipeline:**
1. Documents → TextUnits (chunking, default ~300-1200 tokens)
2. LLM entity extraction from TextUnits (entities + types + descriptions)
3. LLM relationship extraction (source, target, description, weight)
4. Entity summarization (merge duplicate entities across chunks)
5. Hierarchical clustering (Leiden algorithm) → Communities
6. Community report generation (LLM summarizes each community)
7. Embedding generation (entity descriptions, text units, community reports)
8. Output to Parquet + LanceDB

**Retrieval Pipeline:**
- **Global search**: maps query to communities → community reports → LLM generates answer from community summaries
- **Local search**: entity vector search → related relationships + text units + community context → LLM
- **DRIFT search**: hybrid global+local with iterative exploration
- No reranker in core — relies on embedding similarity + graph structure

**Updates/Stale Knowledge:** No built-in update mechanism — indexing is a batch pipeline. To update, re-run indexing (or use incremental indexing in newer versions). No temporal versioning, no conflict resolution. `attributes` dict on Entity for extensibility.

**Multi-Tenant:** None in core — single corpus per index. No user/company isolation.

**MongoDB:** No.

---

### 8. LightRAG (`HKUDS/LightRAG`)

**Data Model/Schema:**
- `lightrag/base.py` — storage abstractions:
  - `StorageNameSpace(ABC)`: `namespace: str`, `workspace: str`, `global_config: dict` — base for all storage
  - `BaseVectorStorage`: `embedding_func: EmbeddingFunc`, `cosine_better_than_threshold: float = 0.2`, `meta_fields: set[str]` — abstract `query()`, `upsert()`, `delete_entity()`, `delete_entity_relation()`
    - [lightrag/base.py#L172-182](https://github.com/HKUDS/LightRAG/blob/main/lightrag/base.py#L172-L182)
  - `QueryParam`: `mode: Literal["local", "global", "hybrid", "naive", "mix", "bypass"] = "mix"`, `top_k: int`, `chunk_top_k: int`, `enable_rerank: bool = True`
    - [lightrag/base.py#L78-90](https://github.com/HKUDS/LightRAG/blob/main/lightrag/base.py#L78-L90)
  - `TextChunkSchema(TypedDict)`: `tokens: int`, `content: str`, `full_doc_id: str`, `chunk_order_index: int`
- `lightrag/types.py` — Pydantic models for LLM extraction:
  - `ExtractedEntity`: `entity_name: str` (title case), `entity_type: str`, `entity_description: str`
  - `ExtractedRelationship`: `source_entity: str`, `target_entity: str`, `relationship_keywords: str`, `relationship_description: str`
  - `EntityExtractionResult`: `entities: list[ExtractedEntity]`, `relationships: list[ExtractedRelationship]`
  - `KnowledgeGraphNode`: `id: str`, `labels: list[str]`, `properties: dict[str, Any]`
  - `KnowledgeGraphEdge`: `id: str`, `type: Optional[str]`, `source: str`, `target: str`, `properties: dict[str, Any]`
  - `KnowledgeGraph`: `nodes: list[KnowledgeGraphNode]`, `edges: list[KnowledgeGraphEdge]`, `is_truncated: bool`

**Storage Backend:** Triple pluggable:
- **KV storage**: JSON files (default), Redis, Postgres, MongoDB (via `KVStorage` abstractions)
- **Vector storage**: NanoVectorDB (default in-memory), HNSW, FAISS, Milvus, Qdrant, ChromaDB, LanceDB
- **Graph storage**: NetworkX (default, in-memory + GraphML persistence), Neo4j, Memgraph
- `workspace` field on StorageNameSpace for namespace isolation
- Storage choice: pluggable to support local-first (JSON/NetworkX) to production (Postgres/Neo4j/Milvus)

**Ingestion Pipeline:**
1. Text chunking (token-based, configurable)
2. LLM entity + relationship extraction (structured output via `ExtractedEntity`/`ExtractedRelationship` Pydantic models)
3. Entity/relationship deduplication and merging
4. Embedding generation (configurable model)
5. Storage to KV (chunks, docs), Vector (entity descriptions, relationships, chunks), Graph (nodes, edges)

**Retrieval Pipeline:**
- **6 modes**: `local` (context-dependent), `global` (global knowledge), `hybrid` (local+global), `naive` (basic RAG), `mix` (KG + vector, default), `bypass` (direct LLM)
- Token budget system: `max_entity_tokens`, `max_relation_tokens`, `max_total_tokens`
- Reranking enabled by default (`enable_rerank: bool = True`)
- Low-level + high-level keyword extraction for retrieval focus
  - [lightrag/base.py#L90-120](https://github.com/HKUDS/LightRAG/blob/main/lightrag/base.py#L90-L120)

**Updates/Stale Knowledge:**
- `delete_entity()` and `delete_entity_relation()` on vector storage — explicit deletion, not versioning
- `drop_pending_index_ops()` for aborting failed batches
- No temporal versioning, no automatic conflict resolution
- Upsert semantics: `upsert()` inserts or updates by key

**Multi-Tenant:** `workspace` field on `StorageNameSpace` — namespace for isolation. Each workspace has its own KV/vector/graph storage instances.

**MongoDB:** Possible via KV storage adapter (MongoDB is listed as a supported KV backend in docs), but not a primary or documented vector store. Not confirmed in core code as a first-class vector store.

---

### 9. nano-graphrag (`gusye1234/nano-graphrag`)

**Data Model/Schema:**
- `nano_graphrag/base.py` — dataclass/TypedDict abstractions:
  - `QueryParam`: `mode: Literal["local", "global", "naive"] = "global"`, `top_k: int = 20`, with per-mode token budgets
  - `TextChunkSchema(TypedDict)`: `tokens: int`, `content: str`, `full_doc_id: str`, `chunk_order_index: int`
  - `SingleCommunitySchema(TypedDict)`: `level: int`, `title: str`, `edges: list[list[str,str]]`, `nodes: list[str]`, `chunk_ids: list[str]`, `occurrence: float`, `sub_communities: list[str]`
  - `CommunitySchema(SingleCommunitySchema)`: adds `report_string: str`, `report_json: dict`
  - `BaseVectorStorage`, `BaseKVStorage(Generic[T])`, `BaseGraphStorage` — abstract storage interfaces
    - [nano_graphrag/base.py#L1-200](https://github.com/gusye1234/nano-graphrag/blob/main/nano_graphrag/base.py#L1-L200)

**Storage Backend:** Pluggable:
- **Graph**: NetworkX (default, in-memory + GraphML), Neo4j (`_storage/gdb_neo4j.py`)
- **Vector**: NanoVectorDB (default, in-memory), HNSW (`_storage/vdb_hnswlib.py`), FAISS, Milvus, Qdrant
- **KV**: JSON files (`_storage/kv_json.py`)
- Storage choice: minimal dependencies — defaults are pure Python (NetworkX, NanoVectorDB, JSON)

**Ingestion Pipeline:**
1. Text chunking (`_splitter.py`)
2. Entity + relationship extraction via LLM (`entity_extraction/extract.py`)
3. Community detection (clustering algorithm on graph)
4. Community report generation
5. Embedding + storage

**Retrieval Pipeline:**
- `local`: entity-centric, retrieves related text units + community context
- `global`: community report-based, maps query to communities
- `naive`: basic vector RAG (top-k chunks)
- Token budget allocation per mode (e.g., `local_max_token_for_text_unit: 4000`, `local_max_token_for_local_context: 4800`)

**Updates/Stale Knowledge:** `filter_keys()` on KV storage to check existing keys. Upsert semantics. No temporal versioning or conflict resolution.

**Multi-Tenant:** `namespace: str` on `StorageNameSpace` — basic namespace isolation. No user/tenant partitioning.

**MongoDB:** No.

---

### 10. Cline (`cline/cline`)

**Data Model/Schema:**
- No code-level schema. Memory Bank = set of Markdown files in project directory:
  - `projectbrief.md`, `productContext.md`, `activeContext.md`, `systemPatterns.md`, `techContext.md`, `progress.md`
- Each file is free-form Markdown with conventional purpose

**Storage Backend:** Files only (Markdown). No database. Memory stored in `.clinerules/` or `memory-bank/` directory.

**Ingestion Pipeline:** Agent reads all memory bank files at task start, updates relevant files at task end. Driven by custom instructions, not code.

**Retrieval Pipeline:** Agent reads files at task start — no programmatic retrieval, no vector search.

**Updates/Stale Knowledge:** Agent updates `activeContext.md` and `progress.md` after significant changes. No versioning, no conflict resolution — manual/agent-managed.

**Multi-Tenant:** None — per-project only.

**MongoDB:** No.

---

### 11. Continue.dev (`continuedev/continue`)

**Data Model/Schema:**
- No explicit schema class — data is implicit in SQLite tables + LanceDB collections:
  - SQLite `files` table: file paths, SHA-256 hashes, timestamps, indexing tags
  - LanceDB collections: `entity_description.lance`, `text_unit_text.lance`, `community_full_content.lance` (in GraphRAG example data) — vectors with metadata (file paths, line numbers)

**Storage Backend:**
- **Vector**: LanceDB (embedded, disk-persistent) — `.lance` files at `~/.continue/index/lancedb/`
- **Relational/metadata**: SQLite at `~/.continue/index/index.sqlite`
- Storage choice: local-first, privacy-centric — code never leaves machine (unless using cloud embedding)

**Ingestion Pipeline:**
1. **Scanning & hashing**: SHA-256 hashes per file, compared against SQLite — only changed/new files processed
2. **Semantic chunking**: Tree-sitter AST parsing → meaningful chunks (functions, classes) — `core/indexing/chunk/code.ts`
3. **Embedding**: `all-MiniLM-L6-v2` via transformers.js (local default), or Voyage AI / OpenAI / Ollama
4. **Storage**: vectors to LanceDB, metadata to SQLite

**Retrieval Pipeline:**
- **Agentic Search** (newer): LLM uses `codebase_tool` to query LanceDB + grep/glob for exact matches
- **Legacy `@Codebase`**: top-k vector retrieval
- Repo mapping for high-level structure before deep search

**Updates/Stale Knowledge:** Incremental via SHA-256 file hash comparison. Changed files re-indexed. No temporal versioning. SQLite tracks file hashes + timestamps for staleness detection.

**Multi-Tenant:** None — per-machine, per-workspace. No user/company isolation.

**MongoDB:** No.

---

## Cross-Cutting Analysis

### Data Model Patterns

| Pattern | Repos |
|---------|-------|
| **Pydantic/dataclass models** (code-first schema) | Mem0, Graphiti, Cognee, GraphRAG, LightRAG, nano-graphrag |
| **SQLAlchemy ORM** (relational schema) | Cognee (Node, Edge, Data tables) |
| **Markdown + YAML frontmatter** (file-based) | OpenWiki, OKF, Cline |
| **Implicit schema** (in storage format) | Continue (SQLite + LanceDB) |

### Storage Backend Patterns

| Pattern | Repos |
|---------|-------|
| **Graph DB only** | Graphiti (Neo4j/Kuzu/FalkorDB/Neptune) |
| **Vector + relational hybrid** | Mem0, Continue (LanceDB+SQLite) |
| **Graph + vector + relational triple** | Cognee, LightRAG |
| **Parquet + vector (file-based)** | GraphRAG (Parquet + LanceDB) |
| **Pure in-memory + file persistence** | nano-graphrag (NetworkX + NanoVectorDB + JSON) |
| **Files only (Markdown)** | OpenWiki, OKF, Cline |
| **In-context + archival** | Letta (memory blocks + external store) |

### Update/Conflict Resolution Patterns

| Pattern | Repos |
|---------|-------|
| **Bi-temporal versioning** (valid_at/invalid_at/created_at/expired_at) | Graphiti only |
| **LLM-driven ADD/UPDATE/DELETE/NOOP** | Mem0 |
| **Hash-based dedup + incremental** | Continue (SHA-256), Cognee (content_hash), Mem0 (MD5) |
| **Git-based versioning** | OpenWiki (gitHead), OKF (git repo), Letta (MemFS) |
| **Batch re-indexing** (no updates) | GraphRAG, nano-graphrag |
| **Agent self-managed** | Letta, Cline |

### Multi-Tenant Isolation Patterns

| Pattern | Repos |
|---------|-------|
| **`group_id` partition key** on every node/edge | Graphiti |
| **`user_id` + `tenant_id` + `owner_id` columns** | Cognee (RLS commented out) |
| **Metadata dict scoping** (user_id/agent_id/app_id) | Mem0 |
| **`workspace`/`namespace` isolation** | LightRAG, nano-graphrag |
| **Per-repository/per-project** | OpenWiki, OKF, Cline, Continue |
| **Per-agent** | Letta |

### MongoDB / Document Store Usage

| Repo | MongoDB? | Details |
|------|----------|---------|
| **Mem0** | ✅ **YES — first-class** | `mem0/vector_stores/mongodb.py`: Atlas Vector Search (`vectorSearch` index type, cosine similarity) + Atlas Search text index. Document schema: `{"_id", "embedding", "payload"}`. Unifies document + vector in single collection. |
| **Letta** | ✅ External only | MongoDB as archival memory tool (agent queries via tool call). Not for internal state (Postgres/SQLite). |
| **LightRAG** | ⚠️ Possible via KV adapter | MongoDB listed as supported KV backend in docs, not confirmed as vector store in core code. |
| **Cognee** | ❌ No | No MongoDB adapter. Uses Postgres/Neo4j/Qdrant. |
| **Graphiti** | ❌ No | Graph DB only (Neo4j/Kuzu/FalkorDB/Neptune). |
| **GraphRAG** | ❌ No | Parquet + LanceDB. |
| **nano-graphrag** | ❌ No | NetworkX/Neo4j + NanoVectorDB/HNSW + JSON. |
| **OpenWiki** | ❌ No | Files only. |
| **OKF** | ❌ No | Files only. |
| **Cline** | ❌ No | Files only. |
| **Continue** | ❌ No | LanceDB + SQLite. |

